comments.body:
I like the idea!

The `Created:` example is a bit tied to auth files. Maybe we can generalize the output to also cover keyrings, authhelpers and whatever the future might bring. I guess it should display which authentication mechanism was used and add some specific (but optional) data to the output, in case of auth files the path.

@QiWang19 @mtrmac WDYT?

@mtrmac @vrothberg @QiWang19 If we just make 

https://github.com/containers/image/blob/master/pkg/docker/config/config.go#L129
func getAuthFilePaths(sys *types.SystemContext) []authPath {

Public then we could retrieve this data.  Would this be acceptable?  Or has this already been discussed?

@mtrmac raised few important and fair points here https://github.com/containers/image/pull/1204#pullrequestreview-638240935 although I had few doubts so just putting it here I might be wrong but please correct me.
* From issue it seems the `-v`,`--verbose` is more of a UX feature for end user afaik so having it on `stdout` should be fine right ?
* What would be an ideal use-case where we would want to have callback/promise associated with `verbose/debug` log spitting human-readable string.

@mtrmac  @rhatdan @lsm5 @TomSweeneyRedHat @vrothberg This got implemented in https://github.com/containers/image/pull/1204 and https://github.com/containers/common/pull/607 and propagated to podman via https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/10690.

There is a add example to  docs PR: https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/10068 (not necessary though)

But I think this issue can be safely closed now.
